  "texts": [
    "As the Nobel Prize in Chemistry 2019 rewards the development of lithiumion batteries (LIB), this world's most essential and powerful energy supply system has significantly changed the global energy distribution.",
    "In recent decades, the environmental protection and energy consumption challenges further pushed the rapid development of LIB.",
    "From the applicationoriented perspective, the top-list challenges faced in current battery research mainly include 1) achieving high-energy-density batteries; 2) discovering advanced solid-state-electrolytes; 3) realizing fast-charging and high-rate performance in batteries; 4) predicting the charge status and full calendar lifetime prediction of batteries; and 5) enabling environmental-friendly recycling of the batteries.",
    "Artificial intelligence (AI) has shown enormous potential to breakthrough these challenges.",
    "This perspective is intended for both battery science researchers seeking to leverage ML techniques in addressing key challenges in the field and ML researchers interested in adapting existing methodologies to the unique requirements and constraints of battery science."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}